Nov 24 2009 	GOOD BUT WITH NOTES	A very pleasant place to stay overall, and we were there a week. Clean and neat. I will list the shortcomings and other than that it was all perfect. No free internet. You can attend a time share meeting and get it free, but otherwise it was $5/day for a wireless hook-up. We stayed in Tower 5 because we asked at check-in where the nicest rooms were, and since this is the new building they directed us there. We were at the end of the long hall on the 7th floor. There is limited parking close to the one elevator, but it is first come and goes fast. Unless you stay in the room all the time you will return at times and have to use their free parking garage. This parking garage is at the opposite end of Tower 5's elevator, and you will have a walk of about 150 yards each way which was a pain to deal with all week. Staff was friendly, but maintenance was invisible. Our room was missing a hair dryer, and when we asked for one (twice) we finally were told they were ordering more and we never did get one.The lazy river was nice, but in November the building blocks the sun on most of it and that made it pretty cool in the shady fall air. We had to pay for an innertube and that was disappointing as it would cost them nothing to throw this in for free. Good location on the strip, but out of the hussle, but within fast striking distance.We would stay there agin.	
