Oct 14 2009 	Great resort! Will go back for sure!!	Just got back a few days ago and had a great time. My family owns a timeshare at Tahiti Village so we got a great deal for the week. We stayed in Tower 5 on the 8th floor. Just had a single room which was very spacious for the 4 of us. We had a nice view of the lazy river from our balcony. They offer a shuttle bus to the strip that leaves every half an hour. The bus has stops at the Tropicana and Treasure Island. The only thing with the bus that we didn't enjoy was that the bus last pick up is at 12:30 AM. But it's not the worst thing in the world, if you stay out late you'll just have to take a cab. The resort is right next to the airport, but suprisingly you dont hear anything from your room. We could hear them from the pool, but not a big deal. The pool area is very nice, and they allow you to bring in food and drinks. No glass, although someone had, and ended up breaking it in the pool. So that was 3 days of no pool because they had to drain, clean and refill it. Some people like to ruin it for others. But I would go back to Tahiti Village again. Great location right next door to the outlets. Very close to Walmart and other shopping. I would recomment this hotel to anyone. Great time. The people who have bad reviews on here dont know what they are talking about. This is a timeshare so like any other timeshare your room doesnt get cleaned every day, only once a week. These are more like condos, than hotel rooms. And yes you may be asked to go to a sales pitch, dont go then. There is no suprise that they want you to buy, so there will be pressure. Oh one bad thing- when we got our room cleaned they forgot a couple of things so we had to call twice to get someone to come back and bring the missing towels, soap ect.	
Oct 13 2009 	Couldn't have been any better!	This was my second trip to Tahiti Village. I loved it the first time &amp; I loved it the second! Our room was lovely and spacious, beds were comfortable, it was very quiet and we slept great. The staff was helpful and very friendly. We were there 4 days, and really didn't need maid service during that time, so didn't miss it. Plenty of towels to last the two of us. We did need some soap, but just ask one of the maids one morning in the hall, and she gave us some from her housekeeping cart. The lazy river is to die for! Get your innertube and float all day. It's so relaxing. (and, yes, there is a $3.00/day charge for the innertube, but who cares?) It was great to be at such a quiet and peaceful place during the day, then go to the noisy and fun casinos at night. (By the way, the free shuttle to the strip is very convenient and the drivers are helpful.) All in all, it was a great time (again!) and I'll definitely go back.	
