Oct 8 2009 	Great Hotel!	We had a group of 4 traveling to Las Vegas for a special birthday occasion. We decided to try the Tahiti Village based on the recommendation of another friend. The hotel is actually a time-share, which is the only real downfall of this place. We booked it as a hotel, and told them we weren't interested in the time-share, and they didn't push it too hard, but there were tours constantly going on, so the place was quite crowded. Our rooms, which were very nice- perfect for families- were on the same floor as the meeting center for the time-share meetings, so our hallways were always crowded. But getting past the time-share, we had a wonderful stay. The rooms are very clean, and comfortable. They are not luxurious, but have everything you would need. Our units were the one bedroom units. They had a kitchenette, living area, bathroom and bedroom. A lot of space for just the 2 of us in each room. The hotel is very easy to find on Las Vegas Blvd, just south of the strip. There is shuttle service provided by Tahiti Village, or ample parking if you have a car. The pool area is wonderful. There are two swimming areas- the beach pool which has an actual sand beach and a lazy river. Both are great fun. Overall, I would stay there again and again, with or without my kids.	
Oct 6 2009 	Excellent great place to enjoy your time in Vegas!	My husband and I recently spent 5 days/4 nights in Vegas with my sister and her husband at Tahiti Village. Our daughter is an owner and she made our reservations. We stayed in the Bora Bora unit which had the bedrm suite with bath and the kitchen/dining/living room combo. It has a king bed and queen sofa. The queen sofa was very nice to sleep on. The biggest thing that we all enjoyed was the jacuzzi tub, which is big enough for two and the steam shower, both were very nice. The photos that you see of this resort are exactly what you seeIf you choose to book a room here you should know:1. Internet... there is no internet in the rooms, but you can connect in a small area by registration or go to Denny's which is on site2. Parking... It is pretty hard to get a parking spot around the towers of the resort, but there is a parking garage and you can enter Tower 5 which is a short walk. They have security that checks it regularly. They called us one nite to tell us we had left our lights on the car.3. Shuttles... they give you a shuttle schedule when you check in and it is quite flexible and the wait isn't bad4. Staff... I read a few reviews that were critical. We found that to be untrue, everyone we dealt with were very friendly and helpful. We ask for extra towels, sheets, coffee, etc. and they were very promt to make sure we had what we needed.5. House keeping... if you are expecting daily housekeeping you will be disappointed. This is not a hotel/motel. You're on your own, unless you spend more the 7 days and then they come in on day 3 or 4 and clean. If you place the trash out in the hall in the mornings they will pick it up and as i said up above, if you need anything...ASK6. Noise... this is in the path of planes taking off and landing, but the only time we really heard anything was when we had the doors of the room open or we were out side and it didn't bother us at all. You are going to hear these sounds no matter where you are in Las VegasWe enjoyed the lazy river, the pool and the hot tub. The hot tub could get a little crowded, but it is open 24/7. AND you will find sand in the pool and hot tub, after all there is a sand beach which is great and it is a tahitian decor. We just went with the theme and had a great time!!!!	
