ong with this picture? You exchange a week and this is what you get. Oh and the main/large pool, I have never seen something so dirty in my life. It was disgusting, we didn’t even put our toes in it! The lazy river was clean and very, very nice!!! Other than the door, the Lazy River was great!!! A huge plus for a family !!!! The shuttle, NOBODY, and I mean NOT A SINGLE staff member could explain the shuttle schedule to you!!!! That was pathetic!! The bus driver got it right, thankfully! (It left early from the strip, thankfully we didn’t depend on it leaving at the scheduled time!) The managers and staff don’t seem to strive for quality at this resort! The concierge, when they give you directions, they don’t give you a map, they tell you what streets to turn down. No sheets with directions. Keep in mind, the “Concierges” appear to work for Member Services, they book tours. They aren’t really a “Concierge” there to give you info about the area. Concierges generally have ample information to give you vs. short answers. I have stayed at some nice resorts and this resort doesn’t get a even one star about the above things I just talked about. Tower 5: if you are booked in Tower 5, expect a lot of walking as you will likely have to park in the underground parking area! The pros: The Lazy River is great, the shuttle is nice (I rather drive, parking is rather easy and less time consuming) and location is wonderful! The unit was nice. The staff at the Lazy River was very nice and would smile at you (hospitality), the shuttle driver was informative nice. The location is ideal, near the strip, near grocery stores, shopping, etc. I can’t say that I would go back. I don’t stay in the unit for much more than to sleep and eat breakfast so too many things stood out in the negative. NOT WORTH THE EXCHANGE!!!!!!!	
