Aug 14 2009 	Would stay here again.	We are consolidated resorts owners, and after hearing about the bankruptcy we were very concerned, but it was very difficult to notice anything different. The hotel grounds and rooms were spotlessly clean and beautiful. We did not hear any noise from the rooms near ours, as was reported by other guests. The parking was convenient and they have a beautiful covered parking garage in addition to parking lots, which was much appreciated in the 110 degree weather. It is a bit of a drive to the strip, but during our week stay we learned to use a couple of the secondary roads rather than Las Vegas Boulevard and could get up and down the strip easily. Just valet parked at whatever hotel we were stayin at.The lazy river was truly wonderful. The hotel charges $3 per day for tubes, but we never paid for any, as guests who were leaving offered their tubes to guests newly arriving and there were always several unclaimed tubes lying around. We had no problem finding chairs in the sun or shade at anytime during the day. Drinks at both the pool and the lazy river were expensive, but you were allowed to bring your own in a cooler. They did sell small ones in the gift shop for $5.00.We rented cars due to the sheer number of people we had with us, so I can't comment on the shuttle service, but we did see Tahiti Village shuttles on the strip when we went. The vans were large and nice looking.We received a mid-week cleaning, and had no problem having any trash picked up if left outside our door within a few minutes.The grill area was very nice and was cleaned thoroughly every morning.We would never have known the ownership was in bankruptcy during our stay and in fact the hotel was booked solid. We couldn't even pay for an upgrade as their was nothing open. We did ask for a later check out, but were refused. We found buying groceries/liquor at the Food for Less much more economical than the Whole Food market and it's just a a short five minute drive. The shopping outlet mall is walking distance (just across the street).I wouldn't hesitate to recommend Tahiti Village to anyone.	
