y for children and the sand is not well confined to that area. It goes everywhere and is really an annoyance. There was also about an inch of sand in the bottom of the spa. When I asked if they were going to clean it out, all I got was a dirty look.And forget about bar or food service! There is a portable bar by the pool and another by the &quot;lazy river&quot;, but no servers. Drinks are $13 for the first and $9 for refills. Available food included chips and ice cream at the bar or a hot dog or nachos at a portable cart....which was out of hot dogs when I wanted one because they're only allowed to have 6 (!!!!) in the cart at a time. And did I mention there are no restaurants in the resort itself? There is Tahiti Joe's just across the driveway and Denny's in the same building and that's it. Tahiti Joe's was horrible! The food was awful, the service was abysmal and cocktails have to go on a separate check because the bar is actually owned by a different company. Concierge service was a joke....yes, they'll book local day trips for you and make reservations, but they also want to sign you up for a sales pitch and when we declined, the concierge became VERY rude and cut off the conversation, even though we were about to ask her to make reservations for us.This place has so much potential, but is a disaster as it is now...I couldn't even get change for a dollar to use the vending machine. And parking?? Horrible! Couldn't get a parking space late one night so parked in guest registration parking and got a nasty note on the windshield and a nasty phone call at 6 am....I guess I was supposed to park on the other side of the resort between Denny's and the fleabag motel next door and walk all the way to my room late at night alone?? NOT! Had to park on a deserted side street each night after that and walk to my room. Scary.	
