Aug 3 2009 	Wonderful Exvhange!	Just returned from a relaxing vacation at Tahiti Village. If you are looking for a cheap deal in exchange for listening to a time share presentation, I would avoid this place, judging from all the other negative reviews. BUT, if you already own somewhere, and understand the difference between a time-share resort and a regular hotel type resort (i.e., time shares don't have maid service, so don't expect it) and are looking to exchange through Interval International, have no fear. Based on the advice here, I requested a pool view, phase II. I was told I could make requests, but they were not guaranteed. Nonetheless, we received an immaculate room on the 7th floor of Phase two. (Tower 5). Not only did we look down on the lazy river, but also we enjoyed a wonderful view of the strip. Beautiful at night! We were never once approached or hassled about a presentation. Our room was quiet, and with the patio door shut, we couldn't hear any outside noise (including air traffic). Open, as we frequently did, we enjoyed listening to the sounds of kids playing in the lazy river. My boys and husband also got a kick out of watching the planes land and take off. The furniture and kitchen were beautiful and new. The only drawback was that there was no separate toilet area, just once large bathroom. No place for me to put on makeup while my husband and older boys took care of business. The grounds were well kept, and we enjoyed both the lazy river and the pool. You could buy drinks and a few light snacks at the pool, but there was no problem bringing your own. We packed a cooler with plastic glasses with lids, and enjoyed our drinks while floating around the pool or lazy river. You have to rent their tubes on the lazy river, $3.00 per day, but in the pool you could use your own floats. The lifeguards were all clean cut and pleasant. There were several nice BBQ areas, with tables and chairs and 4 BBQ's, but I would recommend bringing your own tools. You 