Jul 11 2009 	We will never go back!	We traded our week, so that we could take our children to Tahti Village. My husband and I had taken a tour last year, and thought our children would really enjoy this resort now that the Lazy River had been finished. We had a list of complaints by the end of the week. First of all the main pool was very dirty. I don't know how often it is cleaned, but I did not appreciate floating clumps of hair while I was trying to relax in the pool. Secondly, there need to be more pools for the size of this resort. The pool and the lazy river are way too crowded. The Lazy River is supposed to be for floating around. It was so crowded at times, that it took forever to float around the river just once because there was actually &quot;crowd traffic&quot;. Thirdly, I thought it was inappropriate for the resort to allow all that beer drinking in the lazy river. It got a little wild on the Fourth of July, with some semi drunk guys acting pretty foolishly while families with children were trying to enjoy themselves at the lazy river. Fourthly, not all the dryers were working in the laundry room, causing a backup. Who wants to stay up past midnight doing laundry during their vacation? Complaint #5: the concierge in building five was not helpful at all when I asked him about the local children's museum. He never made eye contact, and the only thing he could do was print out the directions for me. He was very young and inexperienced. Complaint #6: The gyms need to have age rules posted. On one of the days that I was working out, I saw parents dropping off their young children (maybe about 9-10 years of age), and leaving them there to entertain theirselves. I was there to exercise, not supervise other children who could get injured on one of the machines. Complaint #7:Security was too lax. There were lots of people going in and out of the buildings at night, and using the pool that I am positive were not members or resort guests. How could so many people not have a card key to enter the pool areas or the buildings? Complaint #8 (and final one as well) : The internet access was absolutely primitive. I had noticed several people sitting in one section of the lobby using their laptops. Since I did not want to pay to use the computer in the lobby, I was told by someone at the front desk that I was welcome to use my laptop in that section because that is where you could access the internet from the Denny's that is located accross the parking lot. In other words, the resort was not paying for internet access. Even though I knew it was an unethical procedure, I tried it anyway. The internet was extremely slow. It took me 20 minutes to &quot;get in&quot;, and it was through Denny's home page. I went an entire week without retrieving my email.NEVER, WOULD WE RECOMMEND THIS RESORT, AND NEVER AGAIN WOULD WE STAY THERE!!!	
Jul 4 2009 	Had a fabulous time	My husband and I stayed in a 1 bedroom suite (Bora Bora room) along with our two kids (ages 10 and 6). The room was very spacious, more than enough for two adults and two kids. The bathroom was great with two sinks, a hot tub bath, and a standing shower stall. The room had a full kitchen (including pots and pans), dining table, sofa bed, and balcony. There were two TVs (one in the living room and one in the bedroom). We had no problems with any sales people regarding the timeshare tour. We had one message on the phone to pick up the welcome package and that was it. I heard that if you did not want to be bother about the timeshare tour, don't pick up the welcome packet. So we did not pick it up and had not problems. The staff were very responsive to our needs and very helpful.We are a little hesitant about Tahiti Village because of some of the negative feedback left but we thoroughly enjoyed our stay and had none of the problems that peopled have complained about in the previous reviews. The kids loved the pool and we never had problems finding a shady place to sit. The fitness center was OK, small room with old equipment but it was better than nothing. We did not use the shuttle as we drove. We did not have parking problems but we were usually back by 9:00pm. The kids enjoyed M&amp;M World, Paris hotel, Caesar's Palce, and the water show at the Belagio. If you like Nachos go to Margarita Ville (near Flamingo Hotel) and order the volcano nachoes (this thing iis huge and should be shared).	
Jul 2 2009 	Family atmosphere close to the strip and not having to expose the kids with all the visual pollution the strip offers	We recently stayed at Tahiti Village for the first time for a family reunion (approximately 30 people) June 21st week. Our party included several adults and many kids of ages 3-13. We rented 4 different 2 bedroom lockout condos to accommodate our large reunion. We were very impressed with the accommodations. Pros- The condos were very large and had many nice upgrades such as granite counters, full kitchens, washer/dryer and flat screen t.v.'s. It was very clean and perfect! - They have a main pool which was very warm all the time and a lazy river pool which was always cool and refreshing. Both were nice. - Kids play room on 5th floor. Pool tables, air hockey, games, and arts and crafts. A huge plus of entertainment that the kids loved.- Resort offers complimentary shuttle service to and from the strip which was very easy and convenient to use. Much better than driving with the traffic. - There are plenty of grocery stores nearby for stocking up your condo and also an outlet mall next door for shopping.- 5 Barbeque pits provided and were cleaned each am by maintenance. This is a huge plus to have someone else clean out all the prior day grease, cooking scum.Cons- Pools do get crowded by mid morning so we had to get out early to save some chairs. They do offer towel service at both pools. - One negative would be renting the tubes at the lazy river. They charge you $3/person per day to rent and you can’t bring personal tubes. A tip is many are just left lying around to use, yet of course this is not endorced by the guy collecting the $3.- Internet wireless is not working in one of the towers in the back. You have to go to Denny's for wireless access.We would definitely recommend Tahiti Village and will be back. Great family atmosphere close to the strip and not having to expose the kids with all the visual pollution the strip offers (adult billboard advertisements, loud music, and gambling). If you want much R&amp;R, this is the place. If you need to access real-time gambling, stay on the strip.	
