Apr 30 2009 	Unexpectedly "PHENOMENAL" Experience	After all the negative reports of Tahiti Village - I was worried about my stay. However, let me be one of the few to tell you - this resort is beyond beautiful and do not believe the negative reports.I arrived at 1pm (knowing check in was not until 4pm). I was greeted by great service from workers in the lobby. The woman who checked me in went out of her way to ensure I got the perfect room. She asked what building (new or older) and view (strip, standard, pool, or mountain). I chose Building 5 (NEW) pool view. To my surprise our room was ready!! The woman who checked us in was very personable and knowledgeable.After check in - we went to Tahiti Joes for lunch. I had rented a car but did not know where anything was at and was too hungry to look. The greeter at Tahiti Joes was very nice and took our order with ease. We got 2 burgers and fries meals. Here is a complaint: We waited an hour (no lie) for our food to come (we got take out). Furthermore, Tahiti Joes was empty so I could not understand the serious delay. The staff was nice (I won $20 at their slot machine) but that was it. The food was over priced and only average. For those who rent a car, there are many options (the outlet mall which is right across the street [food court], McDonalds and other fast food joints (all within walking distance (bus ride) and driving.Another complaint (though did not bother me) was the groups of visitors whom were doing tours who were being begged to sign their name on the dotted line to purchase a timeshare - the Tahiti Village team would take them to Tahiti Joes and buy them a drink to get them liquored up and sign their name. Avoid this at all costs if you are doing a tour.The room: I got a studio and let me tell you, IT WAS STUNNING!! This is my 4th timeshare room and this one ranks number 1. The studio is the size of a 1 bedroom (really) - it was huge. I had a view of the strip and pool and could see the sun rise every morning. It was great. The bed was super comfortable and the 2 flatscreen tvs were added bonuses. This room is nice for 2 people (a couple), it is cozy and immaculate filled with tropical illustrations. It does not feel like your in the middle of the desert. Be careful though, the standard rooms overlook a dirt field (I think they call that mountain view) - request a pool or strip view.Another complaint is about Building 5 (though this may be consistent in the other buildings as well). If you have a car, you have to park in the garage which is on property but it takes about 10 minutes to get from the garage to your room. Also, there is a LONG (no lie) hallway from outside to the elevators, it goes on forever. When checking in, be ready to carry your bags, groceries a long way. This is only a minor complaint but for those with mobility issues - it may be problematic.Rent a car or not? YES! For me, the convenience of having a car made my vacation even better. However, I can honestly say, the shuttle service (though I did not take it), was seen on property and seems worthwhile. Driving on the strip in April was GREAT!! I have heard the horror stories but it was not bad in anyway. Yes there is traffic, but if you live in any metropolitan city, you can handle the strip. However, if you are going to an event, you should leave 2 hours early (to drive the strip, park the car and get to your location). Speaking of parking, the parking garages at hotels along the strip are FREE - however, they are just as big as the hotels themselves. I found valet to be best (also free) just tip $1 or $2. The only things in walking distance is the outlet mall across the street and gas stations. It is in no way in walking distance to the strip. However, both the airport and rental car facility are next door. Back to Tahiti Village - the sand pool and wave pool are BEAUTIFUL. I did not get to experience it - the weather was cold during most of my stay but I did get to sit at the pool. The chairs are relaxing and areas well kept. Lifeguards were on duty daily and were nice as well. Get ready to be starred at and get photo ops from tours, they are taken to the top of building 5 for an ariel view of property.Housekeeping: Phenomenal, everything I ran out of was replaced within minutes.I did not get to experience any of the activities offered but many were offered. I tried to do the Red Rock Canyon tour through Tahiti Village but was told it was booked solid for 3 weeks. If you know you want to do any tours offered by the resort, book them as early as you can. The concierge were nice (not the greatest).Watch out: Walking around the property (you will get stopped) to take a tour/presentation. Decline nicely and be on your way. Also, on your 2nd day, you will get a call about a &quot;Welcome Package&quot;, DO NOT pick it up. It is a trap for a tour/presentation. Also, for those reports about no maid service, this is a timeshare - that is expected. Also, be on the lookout on the strip from other timeshare presentation people, they will stop you in general conversation and try to get you to attend one, just decline and walk away.In the room - there is no channel line up. The weather channel is not very helpful (it is not local). No internet (very expensive); the channels are good (basic cable).Overall, EXCELLENT experience and already booked a return trip for August.Check out was great.	
