Feb 4 2009 	Great place - Comfortable Well-kept but Rent a Vehicle	I certainly plan to stay here again because the property is very new (completed in August 2008), it's clean, comfortable, well-appointed and reasonably priced.Because we were a group of six, we stayed in the Royal Tahitian suite (combination of the Bora Bora and Moorea suites). The Bora Bora had a full kitchen and steam shower while the Moorea had a half-kitchen and a much smaller bathroom. Both types of suites will sleep four (both come with pull-out sofas), but I would opt for the Bora Bora because the larger space and extra amenities (including a deck) are worth it. If your traveling just as a pair and you don't plan to spend much time in your suite, the Moorea is just fine. Both suites come with two large screen LCD TVs and a DVD player.The only drawback and the reason this property is not a 5/excellent - the location. This is Las Vegas and it's always great to be able to walk out and be a few steps from the action. Tahiti Village is technically on the Strip, but it's definitely not walking distance to the major casinos (not even Mandalay Bay). On the plus side though, it is fairly near a new and very large shopping complex called Town Square.I think a rental car is a necessity (despite the lack of parking spaces), but Tahiti Village offers free shuttles every two hours to the heart of the Strip.Overall, it's a great property. If only it was closer to the other major Las Vegas properties/attractions....	
