Aug 15 2008 	Nice Timeshare	My mom called to reserve her timeshare in Las Vegas and when it was not available for the dates we wanted, she was given availability at Tahiti Village. I was a little nervous after reading the reviews but it wasn't too bad. I loved the rooms. We stayed in 2409/2409A (sleeps 8). There was plenty of room and nice decor. It was also quiet. My mom was worried being so close to the airport and the noise from the pool but once you were inside the room you couldn't hear anything. The lanai was wonderful. It's really big and looked over the pool. We had breakfast out there every morning. There was some hair on towels and food in the track of the sliding glass door. They really don't pay attention to detail, maybe because they have so many units to clean. Overall, we were happy. The parking is horrible. It's not bad if you can get one of the few places up front but if you have to park in the garage, it's very far away. I utilized valet parking when I couldn't find a close spot but valet takes forever! A minimum of 15 minutes to get your car. Ridiculous. There are plenty of hotels on the strip the same size or larger and they get your car to you in less than 5 minutes so I'm not sure what the problem is with valet parking at Tahiti Village. The continental breakfast they offer is a joke. Three juices, pound cake, muffins and coffee. That's it. Nothing nutritional. Denny's was good for breakfast. Tahiti Joes was awful. Not recommended. The entertainment was just as bad. For those of you want the Las Vegas Resort ammenities (casinos, entertainment, restaurants, etc) this is not the place for you. This is a timeshare, so yes, it's going to be more like an apartment complex. The pool is awesome and a great place to cool off. I would recommend this hotel but personally, if I had to pay for it...I would stay elsewhere.	
