Jul 10 2008	The good and just be aware of potential challenges..	It was very hot from June 30 thru July 5th, almost 110 degrees daily, that is not a misprint. However it was tolerable instead of unbearable since it wasn't humid. Premises are nice as advertised. Good water pressure. Steam shower is unique. Steam shower is interesting as it works like a sauna if you are into that kind of stuff. But the shower door opening and closing isn’t smooth, you have to use some force to open and close. Pool area is nice and large. They need to fix the pool basketball rim, they have a volleyball net in the pool area as well. Dennys and Tahiti Joes which is an eating establishment is right next door. Washer/Dryer in the room is a nice convenience. Plates, glasses, utensils all provided. Nice room layout. A very very basic complimentary continental breakfast is provided in Tahiti Joe, Muffins/Pound cake and Juice/Tea/Coffee. The room safe is very very small, cannot fit a laptop.Tahiti Joe hosts some activities like sundae and cookie building for 2 bux. Plenty of pool related activities. Shuttle for groceries twice a week early in the morning. Town Centre is nearby, ½ mile. Access to shops, restaurants, and brand new digital movie theater. Rent a car if you want flexibility otherwise you will be bound to the shuttles and bus system. Local roads and local highways are very very easy to navigate and figure out. No need to be intimidated by the Las Vegas Blvd Traffic. Be warned Red Lights at the intersections seem to take forever to turn green. Literally a two minute drive from the airport car rental place. Might be 10 mins from the Airport itself. Real issue is that as a timeshare place the staff isn’t trained in proper hotel management etiquette. For example the front desk didn't know the difference between Tower 2 and Tower 3, basically they didn't know how to read their own map. Or issues with the Tahiti Village printed directions to attractions to Grand Canyon, Hoover Dam, etc... The Hoover Dam directions are completely wrong. Thank goodness I had enough of my own common sense to figure it out before blindly following them and getting completely lost and wasting time. Another example of confusing situation is the whole shuttle system. Confusion on which bus is designated for owners/visitors and which bus is for the people they want to sell timeshares to. Lastly, I'm an owner, don’t make me go thru an owner update, I just want information and details. So if you want discounts arranged by Tahiti go to the 3rd floor of main building and find the Gifting window to find discounted tickets to shows and stuff. I wish I knew about it earlier, it took them 3 days to finally tell me about it. They also have a ½ price booth in the main lobby but it’s a third party, Tahiti is not affiliated with them. Hope this helps!	
