Mar 11 2008 	Happy with our vacation investment	We bought during pre-construction, and this is our first time staying here. It really is gorgeous. Loved all the palm trees. It was a bit cold for swimming in February even for us Mainers. My husband swam but was hoping for a deeper pool. It's only 3 1/2 ft. More deeper pools are coming in phase 3. The rooms are lovely. Enjoyed the steamer! Everyday! Beware of the steam dryer for your clothes. You need to keep them in for around 120 minutes. I won't go to another &quot;owners update&quot; again. It was just another pitch to trade in my smaller one bedroom unit for another bigger unit. When we said no, the head guy got real rude. Our sales lady was really nice though and didn't pressure us. The shuttle service worked very well for us. Except one time when we went to a 10 pm show and didnt realize the shuttle stopped at 11 on weekdays. Outlet Mall is next door with fantastic buys. Tahiti Joe's nightly rib special is tasty and plenty for lunch next day. Excited about returning and seeing the rest of the resort finished. We toured another resort to compare and are much happier with what Tahiti Village has on site. Although their sales people were nicer when we said no. Great Vacation	
