Nov 4 2007 	Mai Tai Roa Ae!	My wife and I were very pleased with our stay at Tahiti Village. We booked our room through hotels.com ($85 per night) and were pleasantly surprised with the accommodations. The room was very clean and comfortable. Staff was helpful and courteous. There was no pressure put on us to purchase a timeshare. The pool is large and there is plenty of room for sunbathing. There is a Denny's restaurant adjacent to the hotel as well as a new place called &quot;Tahiti Joe's&quot; which is a Tiki bar themed restaurant. (Try their ribs. They are out of this world!) The hotel is about two miles from the main part of the Strip. There is a complimentary shuttle that will drop you off at either Tropicana or The Riviera every half hour. Keep in mind that Tahiti Village is a relatively new place, so they are still working out some of the kinks. When we were there they were having some problems with key cards not working in the pool gates. The only other minor complaint I had was the hotel's proximity to the airport. There are jets taking off overhead continuously. Somewhat loud, but tolerable. We would stay here again. I'd give it a B+	
