Apr 11 2007 	Thumbs up for tahiti village!!	Just returned from a week (4/4-4/11) at Tahiti Village. After reading some not so positive reviews, I was pleasantly surprised. We had a 2 bedroom unit - it was huge with 4 TV's and 2 beautlfully appointed bathrooms with jacuzzi and steam shower. Everything was clean and pool area was spread out. Location is not right in the hustle bustle of the strip which we liked. Shuttle service to strip was every 1/2 hour and reliable. Food at adjoining restaurant (Tahiti Joe's) was Polynesian style and delicious. Staff was friendly. Would definitely return!!	
Apr 9 2007 	Enjoyed Tahiti Village Resort Las Vegas	My husband and I with our two kids just returned from a week vacation at the Tahiti Village Resort in Las Vegas. Let me just say that our two children did not want to leave. The weather was awesome. Everything was pleasant from when we checked-in thru checked-out. We were greeted and assisted right away. We had a large 1 bedroom (Bora Bora) unit, which was very nice and spacious for 4 people, granite countertops and in the bathroom, full kitchen and regular TV with dvd in the living room and huge plasma with dvd in the master BR. Everything was provided. I have to admit it took at least 5 minutes to figure out the washer and dryer combo but it does work just need a little patience. Never had an issue with the keys. We loved the pool and the relaxed atmosphere. It was never crowded. A new restaurant just opened called Tahiti Joes. They were fantastic. Service was just a little slow but food, drinks, and service to the pool were excellent. The pool has a little sandy beach feel where kids can actually bury themselves in sand or make sand castles. Also, you were allowed to bring food, drinks, to the pool which most resorts won't allow. For owners, they had some activities for each day; such as, free lunch one day, face painting the other,, continental breakfast, waffle breakfast, etc... My husband and I felt like we were treated like adults. We were given the option to call them if we wanted to attend a presentation and receive free tickets. We opted not to since we're already owners and not interested in upgrading. No one hazzled us. The place is still under contruction but once it's all finished it's going to be an amazing resort. It will include a lazy river which currently is not built. At first I was very nervous about the location due to the reviews from this website but I'm glad I found out to be otherwise and will definately go back hopefully when it's all completed. I can go on writing about this place but I'll stop here. You do need a car to get around other places than the strip. Definately do the Grand Canyon Expedition Tour and Hoover Dam. We were totally amazed and the kids received an excellent educational experience. If you like additional information do not hesitate to ask via email: brokesinc@yahoo.com.	
Apr 8 2007	Call Me Picky	Okay, I am picky but....How on earth can a resort call itself top of the line without internet access???? The website says free wifi in the lobby. Not so here. You want the internet in your room, you can have it...for $11/day. That’s right per day. Oh, so you forgot your laptop. That's fine. Its only $.50/min. in the business center. Yes, you read right, fifty cents per minute. If the website would just say &quot;we will shake you down to use the internet,&quot; I wouldn't be mad. However, it did (at least admittedly by the staff) say so a few months ago that it was free! So we're past being disconnected from the rest of the world, now everything else should be great. Until the &quot;trap on the steam shower dries out and makes your room smell like sewage.&quot; Yup, seems to be a common problem. The resort claims that if you don't use the steam shower then your room will smell like crap...literally. And it does, for real. All this aside, the rooms are gorgeous, staff excellent and pool is great. You wouldn't realize you are in Vegas when you are on the property. That's a good thing by the way. However, Alan Thicke and Tanya Roberts have a lot of kinks to work out on this property.	
